
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gnome-characters` baraye baz kardane narmafzar-e "Characters" dar GNOME estefade mishavad. Ba in narmafzar, shoma mitavanid har character-e unicode ra peyda konid va dar jaye dige copy/paste konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help` --> ℹ️ Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor.
    🔹 `--version` --> 🔢 Namayeshe version-e narmafzar.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-characters

    🔹 Baz kardane narmafzar-e characters.

    $ gnome-characters --help

    🔹 Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor `gnome-characters`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-characters

    🔹 In dastoor, panjereye narmafzar-e Characters ra baz mikonad, ke shoma mitavanid character-haye unicode ra search va copy konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gnome-characters` command is used to open the "Characters" application in GNOME. This application allows you to find and copy/paste any Unicode character.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help` --> ℹ️ Display the command's help information.
    🔹 `--version` --> 🔢 Display the application's version.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-characters

    🔹 Opens the Characters application.

    $ gnome-characters --help

    🔹 Displays the help information for the `gnome-characters` command.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-characters

    🔹 This command opens the Characters application window, where you can search and copy Unicode characters.

